name: GRAVITY #1
description: "Because there is a law such as gravity, the universe can and will create itself from nothing. Spontaneous creation is the reason there is something rather than nothing, why the universe exists, why we exist..." Said Stephen Hawking once. One minute there was nothing, the next, 500K on HIC ET NUNC. This work marks the first work on HIC ET NUNC as part of the HEN500K celebration. Your support is much appreciated! Gravity in its purest form is a black hole, when you think about it, it is rather poetic. As we might never go inside of a black hole, we still need gravity to keep us grounded, or do we?
